The paper proposes a general purpose active learning algorithm for structured prediction, which can be applied to a variety of tasks or models. The specific example used in the paper is learning to recognize human actions and group activities in video sequences, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The algorithm is based on belief propagation inference, which is commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for labeling data, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Overall, the paper covers a broad range of topics in computer science and machine learning, but the focus on structured prediction and active learning suggests that the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
